Package com.bluegosling.possible

Objects that may or may not have a value.

See: Description

    Fulfillable<T>
    A possible value that can be set exactly once.
    Possible<T>

    Possible.Visitor<T,R>
    A visitor of possible values.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractDynamicPossible<T>
    An abstract base class for possible values that are dynamic, meaning whether a value is present or not can change over the life of the value.
    Holder<T>

Package com.bluegosling.possible Description

Objects that may or may not have a value. These can be used as indirect references, and carry the same API as Optional. Some implementations distinguish between a value being absent vs. being present but null (unlike Optional). Some are mutable (Holder and, to a limited extent, Fulfillable).
